The paper discusses a technique for proving the hardness of problems for classes of the polynomial hierarchy or for PSPACE, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The technique involves simulating existential or universal quantifiers, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions reductions, which are a fundamental concept in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
